cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with 3D hand pose estimation from a single depth image, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a 3D hand model and kinematic parameters indicates that it could be related to robotics, hence cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper also involves exploiting uncertainties, which could be related to probabilistic reasoning and Bayesian methods, suggesting that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves anatomical validity, which could be related to graphics and visualization, suggesting that it could belong to cs.GR (Computer Graphics).
